zed form of Irish Luíseach ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":79,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Lucy of Gloucester was born about 1136, in Gloucester, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Sybil de Neufmarché. She had at least 1 son with William II FitzHerbert 2nd Lord of Norbury. She died in 1220, in London, Middlesex, England, at the age of 85."},"et":{"Abt 1136–1220":"umbes 1136–1220","1130–1163":"1130–1163","1136–1220":"1136–1220","1150–1204":"1150–1204","1170–Male":"1170–Surnud","1100–1143":"1100–1143","Aft 1143":"pärast 1143","1220":"1220","1143":"1143","1163":"1163","1130":"1130","Abt 1136":"umbes 1136","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","1204":"1204","1215":"1215","1136":"1136","1100":"1100","before 1170":"enne 1170","Norbury, Derbyshire, England":"Norbury, Derbyshire, England","London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Norbury, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom":"Norbury, Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Llanthony Secunda Priory, Gloucester, England":"Llanthony Secunda Priory, Gloucestershire, England","Gloucester, Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucester, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1136–1220":"noin 1136–1220","1